The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Rebel fight
                                                                                                               Rebel fight
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, July 15: Home minister P. Chidambaram today told Parliament the Centre had appointed a military adviser to counter the very grave challenge posed by Maoists.        
	The adviser, Brigadier G.S. Dadwal, a serving officer, is now with the Naxalite management division of the home ministry.        
	Todays announcement formally outlines the armys role in planning against Left-wing extremism. We are preparing to take on the challenge, Chidambaram said, adding that details were under wraps for security reasons.                                                                                                                                                                            
